< review>
Great place! There's technically 4 hot springs but 1 of them is secluded from the other 3, smaller and the water is more luke warm. The hike to the springs is relatively easy. Nothing crazy. I went on a Sunday around 11am and there was people already there. It got busier as the day went on. It's a beautiful  spot to relax at for a few hours. Be prepared to smell sulfur(smell of eggs) by the way. PLEASE TAKE YOUR TRASH TOO. Be considerate.</review>

<Review>This is a nice trail. The first quarter of a mile is moderately steep. The trail is uneven and not the easiest to walk. It levels out for the most part after that. At about the two mile mark, it gets really steep. I went up the trail about 1/3 of a mile and we decided to turn around and go back.

This trail isn’t used by many people which is nice. It’s just up the road from Mill Creek which is a nicer trail. But Mill Creek has a lot of traffic.</Review>< Resp>

< Review>
Crystal clear, super soft mineral rich water, just lightly sulfuric, moderately challenging short hike. When you enter the parking lot, remember the trail is to the right facing the river, not the left, lest you go down the wrong trail and a much more difficult trek. Not too busy on a Wednesday afternoon. We got the pools all to ourselves for half an hour.< /Review>

< Review>
There are four pools. One providing a bit of intimacy, and 3 next to the river. When in parking lot, with your back to the road, walk down a bit to the right. You will see stone steps soon and wooden reelings. Shortly before the river there is one pool to the left. The ones at the river are warmer and provide great views. We've met the constructor of the pools there as well. Both naked and textile are welcome.<//Review>

<rating>2< /rating>< Review>
This is one of my favorite places in the world. As a long time local, it kills me to see how popular it's become. Tonight we were there (on a Monday) and there was trash everywhere. Cigarette butts littered the path and tub area. What was once a magical place has become another party spot, which wouldn't be so bad if people respected the space.

Oh, and the bucket is for washing your feet, not for dumping your trash.</Review>

<time>1488360233880</time><rate>4< /rate>< review>
This is one gem of a spot. Visitors from all over the globe to soak and relax in these wonderful hot tubs. I have been here a few times now and have found it to be relaxing and peaceful springs There are many different types of people that frequent Remington. Some gay, some straight, people of color, young and old, so if you have a problem with different visitors that come here, it would be great if you can leave your negative attitudes at home or just don't come here. Some work goes into keeping these hot springs open. People bring cleaning supplies and scrub these hot tubs in order to keep them usable. Please people take out what you pack in. Keeping this area clean is a lot of work when there are just a few maintaining the area while many others just pack in and leave their trash. It is sad to know that people can be so negligent with their trash in this peaceful and serene area. P< /review>

<text>This review is just based on a logistical point of view as a delivery driver, have not tried the food. This location takes an extremely long time to make order regardless of they are for delivery, pick up or ordering to go( no dine in due to covid) . They always only have 3 people working and no more. They use atleast 3 delivery apps..ubereats,doordash and postmates. Each one on their own state unrealistic delivery times. Expect to have items delivered at about an hour to 90 mins. Each time I arrived to pick up an order, they take forever. This is not indicative that they are popular. It is mainly due to their lack of prioritizing and quality. Everything is made to order and made fresh, so that in itself is not a prime situation for delivery. That with them not hiring or not utilizing another person doesnt help...so in the meantime if you are using a delivery app to order do not follow the estimated delivery time on the app they are way off...and if you do order from here make sure to tip good, cause if you dont I guarantee that your order will stay there for a good while and get denied and denied until either you cancel or the restaurant does, and dont blame the drivers for the late or delayed delivery.again this restaurant is not set up to manage their to go orders and honestly im dumb founded that many restaurants havent created better systems to streamline their orders.Better yet if you want to better support the restaurant go in person or order over the phone and go pick it up yourself. We are all in this together</text>< Date>

Pho was not what I expected but I was surprised in a good way. It didnt have the usual authentic pho broth taste but it did have an amazing lemongrass flavor. The spring rolls are a great bargain at 3 instead of 2 for the usual price.  They also have a little lemongrass taste as well as a crunchy straw like roll inside that added an awesome oomph to it. The barbecue beef bahn mi was a let down. There was hardly any beef and it was very thin, plain, and had very little smeared on sauce. I will definitely be back for everything except sandwich.</text>

<rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Just like a Vietnamese McDonald's, this place offers delicious food at a great price. You can get anything here from a banh mi to pho to fried rice. I'm in love with the mon-gu here and the egg rolls. I've had the Banh mis and they are alright but they are buy 2 get 1 free. The drinks are usually buy one get one free but are really sweet and taste like your drinking diabetes... But it's buy one get one free 🤷‍♂️. I peronally havent tried the phone or any of the noddle soup dishes but my friends said they were good They have food that's prepared and can take to go that are amazing the egg rolls and spring rolls  are part of them and they are pretty good. They also have things called chicken chouds which are a marinated chicken in fried dough As far as service goes, the staff are friendly but don't speak that great of English. The restaurant provides parking but the place is usually packed so be warned! The one in Pasadena isn't bad but one of my favorite ones to go to is the one in El Monte. Would recommend this place for a nice quick bite. Nothing fancy but does the job done and taste great!</Review>

<user>117038633845079757760<//user>< user_name>
Troy Pereira</user_name>
<date>1489188896899< /date>< rate>
5</rate>
< Review>
The first thing that I noticed is that its cheap. I ordered two banh mi and two boba for 12$. Thats a good deal for LA. Next was the presentation! Brought out on a plastic but nicely ornate plate was a welcome change from the typical red or blue rectangles of the mall. Not the fanciest I know but perfect for its price range. The food was excellent as well, very flavorful. I had the lemongrass chicken while my wife had the bbq pork. Each had its own distinct flavor that lends itself to a banh mi in all the right ways. I will definitely be back, well worth the 30 min drive.</Review>

<username>James Costanzo<//username><time>1471971662527< /time>< Rating>
4<//Rating>
<review>Pho Banh Mi Che Cali (or 'BMC' for short), is one of my go-to Vietnamese chains here in Los Angeles because of it's great value, delicious yet simple offerings, and quick service.

This location is right next to Pasadena City College (PCC), and is one of the nicer BMC's in terms of space, decor, and cleanliness.They recently updated the inside with bigger tables which is a nice plus.

It's hard to beat the value of BMC, and I typically get the buy 2 get 1 free Banh Mi. At $3.50 each, I can get 3 Banh Mi for just above $7.00 after tax. Banh Mi travel well, so I typically take them on hikes or on a road-trip.  They have traditional choices for their protein, nothing fancy, but all equally delicious. My personal favorite is BBQ Chicken (not the shredded chicken).

This BMC, like all the others, offers the same no thrills simple menu of classic Vietnamese restaurant dishes. This is why I believe BMC excels, because it only offers a few items, makes them delicious, and offers them at a good price/value.

BMC in general earns 4 stars instead of 5, simply because it isn't a "blow your mind away" experience, but simply a great eatery, with good food, at an excellent price.<//review><pictures>None</pictures>< response>
None< /response>

< review>
We have been with Royal security for 6 years or so. Ironically enough we switched to them from another company after they knocked on our, which I would typically not answer, let alone let in. I just had good intuition about Mike and the other technician who were on the other side of my door. Once inside, not only did they match the rate of my previous company, but they also added NINE entry points that weren't armed previously and upgraded our panel at no additional charge just for signing a two year agreement with them. We've been very pleased with our security and when we've had false alarms the response time and procedures have been prompt and thorough. We've since added video security to our home and again, we're completely satisfied with the service. Royal Security comes highly reccomemd from us.</review>

< Review>
This place is located in Campbell. At first I was a bit unsure of taking my car to this place. The location at this spot isn’t spacious and their website needs an update. However, the online reviews with their work of  the clients’ completed pictures speaks for itself.

Nick and his team did an outstanding job to my Toyota Supra. I’ve requested for 30% tint all around for my windows. No complaints with their finished results. The application of the tint film looks clean. No bubbles and high quality of tint usage. Also, lifetime warranty! Satisfied on my end.</Review>

Best tint shop in the Silicon Valley!

Nick and team were amazing. I got the high quality work, quick service, and fair cost I was looking for. I was hesitant at first because they don’t have the fancy website and big ornate buildings like other expensive tint shops. After talking to Nick and seeing the work his team was doing in their shop, I was convinced they could deliver what I was looking for.

After only a few hours of hard work, my Tesla Model S P100D was immaculate with matching ceramic tint all around as well as my windshield which we added a light tint w/ UV protection. His technicians are first class and delivered first class work. I am extremely pleased and would recommend them to anyone with a high end car looking for excellent work in a short amount of time and at a great cost.< /review>

< text>
We've had Heather's Home Cleaning come to our house twice a month for the past year and a half. I originally had her staff come to clean after I had a major surgery, intending to stop once I was healed, but we have loved them so much we have never stopped. We have had several different people and they have all done an excellent job. We leave an itemized list each week, detailing what we would like done, and it's always done well. Samantha has even gone above and beyond, doing things that weren't on her list to do -- like putting new sheets on a bed. I had put the fresh sheets on the top of the bed, expecting to do it myself when I got home, and she instead did it for me without being asked -- it was such a wonderful and unexpected surprise. Rescheduling whenever we need to is a breeze. I have always felt safe having her staff in my home, and I love the feeling of coming home to a clean house on the days that they come to do cleaning.<//text>

< text>
Life-changing. After multiple attempts over the course of YEARS to make Handy work, I just couldn't take it anymore. I came to Google, and - voila - Cleaning Tribe popped up.

Prices were reasonable, reviews were fantastic...so we gave it a shot.  Nearly a year later, I am the happiest camper (in the cleanest apartment). Our cleaner shows up dutifully each month, loves to give our cats a treat, is always on time or early, and - most importantly - leaves our apartment spotless.

The customer support is friendly and efficient when we've had to arrange for alternate ways for our cleaner to get in or had general questions.

Make the switch, people.<//text>

<Text>WARN YOUR FRIENDS AND FAMILY...Burlington will not stand behind their defective products.  You are basically stuck with a product that doesn't work for you.

BEWARE!  BURLINGTON COMPANY POLICY STATES that if you purchase clothing that fit in the dressing room, yet shrunk when you washed it, BURLINGTON WILL NOT ALLOW YOU TO RETURN IT.

Which translates to - Burlington will not make good on their defective products.  If it fits in the fitting room, yet shrinks out-of-control, the buyer is stuck with the clothing.  Burlington will not accept it.

How do I know this?  I returned $100+ clothing, just 24 hours after my purchase, because it outrageously shrunk.  Thus, I am unable to wear it.

Went to go return the items and was told by a Burlington employee that they cannot return items because they were washed.  I told them, "it fit in the fitting room".  THEY WILL NOT RETURN THE SHRUNK CLOTHING.

You know what they told me I could do with the shrunk clothing? ..."DONATE IT, BECAUSE WE CAN'T RETURN IT.  IT'S OUR POLICY."

You know why it's "just Burlington now?".  Because the brand turned into "just" a MARSHALLS or "just" a TJ MAX or "just" a ROSS.  With a very unfair return policy.<//Text>< Pics>

</record>
</dataset><record>
<GmapID>0x80ea4206a3067919:0xdee3c0e9bdd1081e< /GmapID><user_id>104589973157535455857<//user_id><Response>None</Response><Pics>None<//Pics>< username>
Al Sharp</username>
< review>
One of my preferred places to shop for clothes. The biggest out of the big three; Marshalls, TJ Maxx, and of course, Burlington Coat Factory.
While it may be my favorite, this store has its flaws. Shopping here is usually a hit or miss, sometimes you end up with 20 items in your shopping cart, and sometimes you wind up with just 3. You just have to get lucky when going here because it can filled with a variety of clothing one day, to one day being empty.
This place can also be a little more organized, there is often large or XL shirts in the medium section, and so on. It really sucks because I often find shirts that I really like but aren't my size, I run into them for the simple fact that they are misplaced in my section! Woman clothing is usually always misplaced in the guy area as well. This place is supposed to be a step above Ross, which I'm typically finding more organized these days. ALWAYS make sure to look at the tag to make sure it is for the correct gender, and size. Clothing is never organized after being tried out by other customers, you often find pants not properly hung by their hangers with their zippers and buttons undone. I also recommend you inspect the clothing you're planning on buying for any tears, or defects, so be very careful in the clearance section because that's usually the case with dirt cheap clothing from brands that sell for $8 and below. Miscellaneous items usually get opened, and sometimes ruined by other customers. During the Christmas season, every coffee maker, speaker, shave kit, or just about anything in packaging was opened by other customers and the employees don't do anything to stop customers from ruining the product's packaging. That can be a good or bad thing depending on what person you are, as items that have been opened usually get a mark down in price, but in my opinion, it makes the store look filthy. I've shared many negatives, and I still rate this place a 4 star for the fact that the clothing, and just about anything else is always priced right. No pair of pants, or shirt that I've found is priced over $30. They carry well known brands like Michael Kors, Calvin Klein, Levi's, Nike, Addidas, Ralph Lauren, and so on, and all for a reasonable price.<//review>
